===Glyph origin===
{{Han etym}}
Possibly a {{Han compound|爻|六|c1=p|c2=p|ls=psc|nocap=y|tr=*gˤruk|tr1=*gˤraw|tr2=*C.ruk}}. Later, {{och-l|*𦥑|tr=*kuk}} was added to form {{och-l|*𦥯}}, and a semantic {{och-l|*子|child}} was added for differentiation.

In the modern form, {{zh-l|*六}} has corrupted to {{l-lite|zh|sc=Hani|冖|t=cover}}, and the hands {{zh-l|*𦥑}} around the {{l-lite|zh|sc=Hani|爻}} have become connected with the 冖. ''{{w|Shuowen}}'' regards {{och-l|*𦥑|tr=*kuk}} as the phonetic component in the character, which may be true according to some Old Chinese reconstructions such as that of {{w|Pan Wuyun}}'s, though probably not others.

See also the top component of {{zh-l|*覺}}, which is a contraction of {{zh-l|*學}}.

===Etymology 1===
{{zh-forms|s=学|alt=斈,𢻯,𡕕,𣁃,𫝯,𭓕,𭓘}}
Endopassive/volitional derivation of {{och-l|覺|to become aware|id=2}} ({{zh-ref|Sagart, 2004}}; {{zh-ref|Schuessler, 2007}}; {{zh-ref|Baxter and Sagart, 2014}}). Ultimately from {{inh-lite|zh|sit-pro|*kruk||to [[rouse]]; to [[awaken]]; to [[disturb]]}}.

